messages.message:
Patch Set 21:

> One more thought about type being like magic instead of low and
 > consecutive numbers/indexes, if we do so we may end-up wit quite
 > big and sparse foreign_type_name[] arrays...

I think if we allow numeric types then they need to be far away from the enumerated types.  We can always handle this in an array like:

 struct lov_foreign_types {
         __u32       lft_type;
         const char *lft_name;
 } = {
     {   .lft_type = 0x0001, .lft_name = "daos" },
     {   .lft_type = 0x0002, .lft_name = "lhsm" },
     {   .lft_type = 0x1234, .lft_name = "chaos" },
     :
     :
 };
